&gt;Hi,
&gt;
&gt;We are investigating replacing our in-houser harvester with an open 
&gt;source harvester and are seriously considering Heritrix. 
&gt;  
&gt;
Nice to hear.

&gt;I was wondering if there is a way to define and send heritrix a job 
&gt;without going through the web UI. We have some existing interefaces 
&gt;that I am pretty sure we are going to want to keep, because they are 
&gt;very simple. 
&gt;
&gt;The Heritrix interface is very nice, and I can seeing making use of 
&gt;it as well, but it does require a fairly sophisticated user. 
&gt;
&gt;I would be interested to know if there is a way to run heritrix as a 
&gt;service rather than as an applicaiton.
&gt;
&gt;  
&gt;
We intend to spend better packaging Heritrix so it can be more easily 
embedded by other apps but in the meantime, checkout how Heritrix sets 
up the selftest.  See here: 
http://crawler.archive.org/xref/org/archive/crawler/Heritrix.html#584.  
The bulk of this method is launching a webapp for the selftest to go up 
against but its the rest is a fairly contained example of a crawl setup 
and launch without use of the UI.

